    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Poles mounted with hooks on one end that are used to pull or push a boat to or from another boat or fixed object. Usually the working part is comprised of a half rounded, pointed hook used to pull, and a straight point used to push. These are forged together on a socket.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
